&lt;p&gt;My colleague, Nick Hill helped me find that you can find the &lt;em&gt;common reductor&lt;/em&gt; by repeatedly differentiating the polynomial with respect to \(dx\):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;\[\dfrac {d}{dx} (5x^3+3x^2-10) = 15x^2 + 6x\]
\[\dfrac {d}{dx} (15x^2 + 6x) = 30x + 6\]
and finally:
\[\dfrac {d}{dx} (30x + 6) = 30\]&lt;/p&gt;

